## Recommended Order

1. **Phase 1** (TTBFormService): Operation-driven column for movement lines. Low risk.
2. **Phase 2** (Packaged beer + dual tracking): Packaged beer items (ea, volume_per_unit), TTBFormService ea→bbl conversion, Mark Production Complete packaging flow.
3. **Phase 3** (Merge): Remove Racking view and Packaging modal; packaging lives in Mark Production Complete. Deprecate packaging_runs; ledger is source of truth for Line 9/10.
4. **Phase 4**: Location stage clarification as needed.

---

## Summary


| Current                              | Proposed                                                                |
| ------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Column from location stage           | Column from operation_type (racking → keg, bottling → case)             |
| Location stage = primary             | Location stage = at-rest inventory only                                 |
| Racking + Packaging = separate flows | Packaging = Mark Production Complete; ledger entries created from there |
| packaging_runs = metadata, no beer   | Ledger is source of truth; packaging_runs deprecated                    |
| Beer = volume only (bbl)             | Bulk beer (bbl) + packaged beer (ea with volume_per_unit for TTB)       |


This rework makes TTB reporting align with how brewing actually works: the process defines the form (bulk → keg → case), not the storage bin. Packaged beer is tracked by count (kegs, cases) for operations while TTB gets volume via conversion.